==Japanese==
{{ja-kanjitab|[[象]][[形]]}}
===Noun===
象形 (しょうけい, shōkei)

# One of the '''six principles''' ([[(六書)]]) for composing Chinese characters: making characters in the shape of what they represent, as [[hieroglyph]]s. For example, [[火]], [[山]], [[犬]]. This is the most fundamental way to make a character.

===See also===
*[[指事]]

